package.name: DataAwareExplorer
package.desc: Provides the Multi-perspective Explorer (MPE). Explore the data-, resource-, time- and control-flow perspective of a Petri net given an event log. This plug-in starts an interactive tool to discover data-aware models, analyse them and check the conformance according to event data. It integrates functionality of the packages 'DataAwareReplayer', 'DataPetriNets' and 'LogEnhancement'. The 'GraphViz' package is used for graph visualization. The MPE is described in the BPM'15 demo paper: http://ceur-ws.org/Vol-1418/paper27.pdf
package.author: Felix Mannhardt

package.name: DataAwareCNetMiner
package.desc: An interactive data-aware process discovery tool based on the ideas of the Heuristics Miner combined with classification techniques. The Data-aware Heuristic Miner (DHM) implements a process discovery method that uses the data attributes to distinguish infrequent paths from random noise by using classification techniques. Data- and control-flow of the process are discovered together. Moreover, an updated version of the standard Flexible Heuristics Miner is included.
package.author: F. Mannhardt

package.name: XESLite
package.desc: XESLite provides solutions to manage large event logs, which are compatible with the OpenXES interfaces. XESLite can be used as drop-in replacement of OpenXES. XESLite provides three importers: Automaton, In-Memory, and MapDB Database. XESLite is describes in the BPM Center Report: F Mannhardt (2016). XESLite - Managing Large XES Event Logs in ProM. BPMCenter.org. BPM-16-04. BPM Center Report. Moreover, it also provides an indexed version of an XLog (XIndexedLog), which can be searched efficiently with the use of indexes.
package.author: F. Mannhardt
